<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 13 at 8:56AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...CAUTIOUS TRAVEL IS ADVISED FOR REDUCED VISIBILITY AND SNOW-
COVERED ROADWAYS THIS MORNING...
WEATHER...
* Winds around 20 mph gusting to 40 mph will result in blowing
snow within snow shower activity through this morning.
* New accumulations of up to an inch are possible through early
this afternoon.
* Air temperatures will hold in the mid 20s.
IMPACTS...
* Blowing snow will result in rapid reductions of visibility to
less than one mile.
* The stronger winds may lead to drifting of snow on roadways
particularly in locations with open exposure.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Motorists are urged to use caution and account for variable
driving conditions by slowing down and allowing extra time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
